THE OBJECT OF GEAR WORKS
------------------------
The object of Gear Works is to convert 12 of the most
famous monuments of the ancient and modern world
into clocks. Each monument is divided into several levels,
and each level can have up to four Play Areas. You will
place gears within the Play Area that will convert the
monuments into clocks.

A plan of the current monument you are working on will
appear at the beginning of each level. The flashing
rectangles in the monument corresponds t the current
level of the monument you are working on.
Each rectangle represents one Play Area.


SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS
-------------------
AMIGA 500, 600, 1000, 1200 , 2000, 2500, 3000, 4000
AMIGA DOS 1.3 of Higher
MEMORY REQUIRED: 512K Minimum
SUPPORTS: Disk Drive, Hard Drive, Joystick

LOADING INSTRUCTIONS
--------------------
Plug the Joystick into port 2 of your computer.
Insert disk into DF0: and turn on the computer.

HARD DRIVE INSTALLATION
-----------------------
To install this program create a directory called
"GWorks" on your hard drive, then copy the contents
of this disk to that directory, you do not have to copy
the S: directory or disk icon, as they will not be
needed.

To run the program open a CLI or SHELL window, CD to
the "GWorks" directory and then type GearWorks and
press RETURN. The program will now load and run.

